                  "title": "Acid Exposure",
                  "short": "Stomach contents irritate the esophagus.",
                  "detail": "The esophagus is not built to handle repeated acid exposure. This can create burning, sour taste, regurgitation, throat irritation, cough, or hoarseness."
              },
