    "emotionalRoot": "Pride, stubborn ego, and an inability to bend or submit to life's flow. Fear of moving forward or making a pivot.",
    "metaphor": "Rather than bending with the wind of change, you choose to crack and shatter at the joint.",
    "physiologicalDescription": "Chronic emotional tension alters your gait and muscular balance, specifically in the quadriceps group (vastus medialis vs. vastus lateralis). This muscular imbalance may contribute to improper tracking of the patella, potentially interacting with cartilage wear and increasing inflammatory sensitivity.",
    "sarcasticAdvice": "Obviously, it is your 'unwillingness to bow before the divine.' It surely isn't your tight IT bands, your completely worn-out sneakers with zero arch support, or you jumping straight into heavy squats after 6 months of absolute sedentarism.",
    "mindfulnessPrompts": [
      "In what area of my life am I stubbornly resisting making a necessary compromise?",
      "Am I afraid of taking the next physical or metaphorical step in my career or relationship?"
    ],
    "physicalTherapyTip": "Perform foam rolling on your tensor fasciae latae (IT band) and quadriceps. Strengthen your vastus medialis with straight leg raises.",
    "medical_safety": {
