          "witty": {
              "metaphorTitle": "The Retired Mall Cop at the Garden Center",
              "metaphorText": "Your immune system is now a retired, paranoid mall cop who was fired from the mall and now works as a greeter at a garden center. He has a whistle around his neck, a flashlight with dead batteries, and a binder full of suspicious persons that includes every living plant, animal, and dust mote in a three-mile radius.\n\nYour mast cells are his trigger finger. Every time a pollen grain floats past, not attacking, just existing, just doing its botanical job of making baby plants, the mall cop screams CONTACT and hits the alarm.\n\nHistamine floods the scene. Your nose becomes a faucet. Your eyes swell. Your throat tightens like someone filed paperwork to temporarily close the airway.\n\nBut here is the absurd part: there is no intruder. It is pollen. It has no agenda. It does not know you exist. It just wants to find another flower.\n\nYour mast cells are not fighting an enemy. They are fighting the memory of an enemy. Somewhere in your life, your nervous system installed a security system that never got the memo that the war ended.\n\nNow you sneeze at sunshine. You itch at air. The mall cop is standing in the gardening aisle macing a rose bush, and you are paying for the cleanup.\n\nThe garden center has a break room with a coffee mug that says WORLD'S OKAYEST DEFENDER. The microwave has been beeping for three years. No one has turned it off.\n\nThe mall cop has a schedule he wrote himself: ALERT, ALL SHIFT, EVERY SHIFT. His binder has tabs labeled POLLEN, DUST, MOLD, and UNTITLED, PROBABLY ALSO DANGEROUS. The untitled tab has four hundred pages.\n\nThe worst part? The mall cop reports directly to you. You sign his paychecks. You wrote the schedule. You gave him the binder. Every time you brace for the worst, every time you assume the other shoe will drop, every time you scan the room for threats, you train the mall cop. And the mall cop is just following orders.",
