ollen is not your mother. The pollen is not your father. The pollen is just pollen. It is not out to get you.\n\nTeach your body that the war is over. Teach it with breath. Teach it with rest. Teach it with slow exhales that say I am safe. Teach it by not bracing. Teach it by not scanning. Teach it by letting yourself believe, for one second, that the world is actually okay.\n\nThe world is not perfect. Not predictable. Not always kind. But okay enough. The threat level is green. Your mast cells are still on red. Write the memo. Deliver it. Breathe it into your body until it believes you.\n\nArmor down or stay reactive. Charming little choice, that one.",
