      "physiologicalDescription": "Belly weight can involve subcutaneous fat, visceral fat, bloating, fluid, insulin resistance, hormones, sleep, medications, stress, diet, activity, genetics, alcohol, menopause, thyroid issues, or other medical conditions.",
      "sarcasticAdvice": "This is not solved by hating yourself in front of a mirror. Shockingly, shame remains a terrible personal trainer.",
      "mindfulnessPrompts": [
          "What am I carrying around my center?",
          "Where did protection become storage?",
          "What health data do I need instead of shame?",
          "What is one safe, boring, repeatable action I can actually do?"
      ],
      "physicalTherapyTip": "Central weight changes deserve a whole-person review: sleep, stress, food pattern, activity, alcohol, medications, labs, waist circumference, blood pressure, glucose/A1c, lipids, thyroid, and medical history.",
