              "witty": {
                  "label": "Comedic & Witty",
                  "title": "The Storage Unit With Too Many Boxes",
                  "paragraphs": [
                      "Your belly is a storage unit that has been collecting boxes for years.",
                      "Some boxes are food patterns. Some are sleep debt. Some are stress hormones. Some are genetics. Some are medications. One box is labeled I DON'T KNOW, I JUST LIVE HERE.",
                      "The manager keeps saying JUST ONE MORE BOX while the walls bulge and the floor creaks.",
                      "There is a CLOSED FOR CLEANING sign on the door. It has been there so long the sign now pays utilities.",
                      "The fix is not screaming at the boxes. The fix is inventory: labs, sleep, stress, food rhythm, movement, alcohol, medications, and what life keeps asking you to store.",
                      "Then one box leaves. Not all. One. Humanity hates boring consistency, which is exactly why it works."
                  ]
              },
              "brutal": {
                  "label": "Brutally Honest",
                  "title": "The Fortress Reality Check",
                  "paragraphs": [
                      "You may have a belly-weight problem. You may also have a protection-and-storage pattern.",
                      "Do not use this as permission to hate your body. Your body has been trying to keep you alive with the tools it had.",
                      "Medical factors matter. Labs matter. Sleep matters. Medications matter. Alcohol, pain, stress, depression, hormones, and food access matter.",
                      "Symbolically, ask what you are storing at your center.",
                      "What fear became a buffer? What shame became a routine? What exhaustion became a snack pattern? What loneliness became a second dinner?",
                      "The answer is not punishment. It is data, rhythm, movement, sleep, food that supports you, and one honest boundary at a time.",
                      "Unload the storage unit or keep paying rent on a fortress you never wanted. Your choice."
                  ]
              }
